cs.CR, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SE 

The paper discusses the intersection of security and machine learning, specifically focusing on computer vision techniques for malware detection. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses the use of deep neural networks for classification, which falls under cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of interpretation frameworks for extracting explanations, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the importance of addressing the resiliency of the malware detectors, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SE (Software Engineering).
